Mathematics for Engineers
By W. N. ROSE, B.Sc. Eng. (Lond.)
Part I.
Demy 8vo, 510 pages. 257 Figures, with over 1200 set and worked examples. Price 9/6 net.

Contains chapters on: 
- Equations; 
- Mensuration; 
- Gradated Algebra; 
- Plane Trigonometry; 
- Calculation of Earthwork Volumes; 
- Plotting of Difficult Curve Equations; 
- Determination of Laws; 
- Construction of Practical Charts, etc., etc.

"The book treats with practical applications of mathematics to engineering problems . . . an excellent laboratory manual."
